<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 11 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTO-1X707LL/DLL/MLL AND RTO-1X709MLL MODELS - INSTALL -
        COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="10">
        <title>COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the countershaft assembly vertical on a clean, flat surface. If previously removed,
                use a suitable driver and maul to install the countershaft bearings (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020n9">Figure 239</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020n9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020n9" filename="../figg13/G13020n9.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 239. Install Countershaft Bearings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mark each countershaft for correct timing. Locate the "O" stamped on the countershaft and
                mark the tooth with highly visible toolmaker's dye or paint (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020n9">Figure 239</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn the countershafts so that the two marked teeth on each LO range gear are towards the
                middle (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020o0">Figure 240</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020o0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020o0" filename="../figg13/G13020o0.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 240. LO Range Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align the output shaft between the countershafts and match the timing marks (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020o0">Figure 240</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the range yoke offset side facing down, install into the synchronizer sliding slot.
                Install the reduction yoke in the sliding clutch on the output shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020o1">Figure 241</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020o1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020o1" filename="../figg13/G13020o1.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 241. Reduction Yoke</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lay the auxiliary housing front face down on a clean, flat surface. Install the bearing race
                in the bearing bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020o2">Figure 242</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020o2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020o2" filename="../figg13/G13020o2.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 242. Install Bearing Race</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Temporarily install the rear bearing cover with two (2) bolts
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020o3">Figure 243</hotlnk>
                and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020o4">Figure 244</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020o3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020o3" filename="../figg13/G13020o3.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 243. Install Rear Bearing Cover</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f13020o4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020o4" filename="../figg13/G13020o4.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 244. Output Shaft Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the auxiliary housing over the countershaft assemblies and the output shaft assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020o4">Figure 244</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the bearing races (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020o5">Figure 245</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020o5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020o5" filename="../figg13/G13020o5.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 245. Bearing Races</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install each auxiliary countershaft retaining strap with two 3/8 inch NC x 1 inch and one
                3/8 inch NC x 2-1/2 inch clean bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020o6">Figure 246</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020o6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020o6" filename="../figg13/G13020o6.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 246. Auxiliary Countershaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the rear bearing cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020o6">Figure 246</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure the output shaft bearing spacer is on the output shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020o6">Figure 246</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Heat the rear output bearing cone and install the bearing, tapered side down, on the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020o7">Figure 247</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020o7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020o7" filename="../figg13/G13020o7.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 247. Install Bearing - Tapered Side Down</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position a new gasket on the rear bearing cover mounting surface (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020o8">Figure 248</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020o8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020o8" filename="../figg13/G13020o8.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 248. New Gasket</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the rear bearing cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020o8">Figure 248</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Eaton/Fuller sealant #71205 or Loctite 242 to the retaining bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the six (6) retaining bolts, and tighten to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#8226;m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020o8">Figure 248</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
